WEBVTT

1
00:00:19.208 --> 00:00:21.291
<i>There. you should have enough ammunition.</i>

2
00:00:21.375 --> 00:00:23.458
<i>Anything else you need?</i>

3
00:00:23.541 --> 00:00:25.250
- People.
- Oh?

4
00:00:25.333 --> 00:00:27.375
I had to get rid of a drunk today.

5
00:00:27.458 --> 00:00:29.333
- but that's not your problem.
- No. no.

6
00:00:29.416 --> 00:00:31.666
But something else might be.

7
00:00:31.750 --> 00:00:32.666
What?

8
00:00:32.750 --> 00:00:35.875
There's a rumor that the Dearpmis guy
who's in the hospital

9
00:00:35.958 --> 00:00:37.625
has been talking to the police.

10
00:00:39.333 --> 00:00:40.291
I see.

11
00:00:41.166 --> 00:00:42.625
That's not good.

12
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:46.291
Thanks for telling me. See you later.

13
00:01:06.375 --> 00:01:07.375
<i>Yes?</i>

14
00:01:07.458 --> 00:01:08.458
Yes. it's me.

15
00:01:10.291 --> 00:01:12.041
We might have a problem.

16
00:02:00.166 --> 00:02:03.833
<i>The typical serial killer is a man.</i>

17
00:02:03.916 --> 00:02:05.000
<i>He is white.</i>

18
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:08.208
He's between 24 and 40 years old.

19
00:02:08.291 --> 00:02:10.083
He prefers to work alone.

20
00:02:10.166 --> 00:02:12.666
He could also be working with others.

21
00:02:12.750 --> 00:02:14.416
for example in pairs.

22
00:02:15.208 --> 00:02:18.333
But if there are mutilations. like here.

23
00:02:18.416 --> 00:02:22.541
it is a clear sign
that he is working alone.

24
00:02:23.666 --> 00:02:24.916
The first victim

25
00:02:25.541 --> 00:02:29.375
is chosen by the murderer
in an environment he's very familiar with.

26
00:02:31.500 --> 00:02:32.750
Fifth floor.

27
00:02:35.541 --> 00:02:38.583
So the classic victim
would be his own mother.

28
00:02:39.625 --> 00:02:42.416
Rituals are something people think
are always

29
00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:45.333
connected to serial killings.
but it's not true.

30
00:02:45.416 --> 00:02:47.458
But if there are rituals.

31
00:02:47.541 --> 00:02:50.375
there is almost always a serial killer.

32
00:02:52.708 --> 00:02:56.833
We distinguish between
two different types of serial killers.

33
00:02:56.916 --> 00:02:59.833
The psychopathic and the sociopathic.

34
00:03:00.375 --> 00:03:04.750
The psychopath does not have a job.
he does not have an education.

35
00:03:04.833 --> 00:03:09.041
He has a long criminal record.

36
00:03:09.125 --> 00:03:10.875
and he is an easy suspect.

37
00:03:10.958 --> 00:03:14.250
The sociopath seems well functioning.

38
00:03:14.333 --> 00:03:16.958
intelligent. well-adjusted.

39
00:03:17.041 --> 00:03:18.875
We need to catch him first.

40
00:03:18.958 --> 00:03:21.750
Do you have anything
that we can use practically?

41
00:03:21.833 --> 00:03:23.375
We'll get to that. Waaler.

42
00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:27.875
The act of killing a person takes time.

43
00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:31.750
So it's not the same
if it happens during the week

44
00:03:31.833 --> 00:03:34.791
or during a weekend or a holiday.

45
00:03:34.875 --> 00:03:36.791
Because the latter could suggest

46
00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:39.625
that the killer has a job.

47
00:03:39.708 --> 00:03:44.166
And might in turn suggest
that we're dealing with a sociopath.

48
00:03:44.250 --> 00:03:46.500
So when our guy kills
during summer vacation.

49
00:03:46.583 --> 00:03:50.166
it suggests that he has a job
and is a sociopath?

50
00:03:50.250 --> 00:03:51.458
Maybe.

51
00:03:52.083 --> 00:03:54.000
Is that practical enough. Waaler?

52
00:03:54.083 --> 00:03:57.250
Yes. I think it would be good
if you could talk

53
00:03:57.333 --> 00:03:59.500
about this case specifically.

54
00:03:59.583 --> 00:04:01.291
Well. we have three murders.

55
00:04:01.375 --> 00:04:04.000
Two murders.
Lisbeth Barli is only missing so far.

56
00:04:04.083 --> 00:04:07.291
I'm sorry. but we have three murders
without a doubt.

57
00:04:08.333 --> 00:04:12.000
And they have been committed
within the same amount of days.

58
00:04:12.625 --> 00:04:15.666
The ritual of mutilating
and decorating the corpse

59
00:04:16.166 --> 00:04:18.791
has been followed all three times.

60
00:04:19.291 --> 00:04:22.708
That suggests that we are
in an early stage with control.

61
00:04:22.791 --> 00:04:24.833
Choice of victim and crime scene?

62
00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:27.333
Yeah. you may be right about that.

63
00:04:27.416 --> 00:04:28.791
Right about what?

64
00:04:28.875 --> 00:04:31.833
That the choice of victim and crime scene

65
00:04:31.916 --> 00:04:33.958
actually suggests the opposite.

66
00:04:34.041 --> 00:04:35.375
How so?

67
00:04:35.458 --> 00:04:39.666
The first murder. Camilla Loen. happened
in her apartment. where she lives alone.

68
00:04:39.750 --> 00:04:41.625
He can get in and out

69
00:04:41.708 --> 00:04:44.958
without risking
being caught or identified.

70
00:04:45.041 --> 00:04:48.791
Second murder. he kidnaps Lisbeth Barli
in a residential neighborhood.

71
00:04:48.875 --> 00:04:52.000
during the day. probably in a car.
cars have license plates.

72
00:04:52.083 --> 00:04:55.958
He's starting to take risks.
And the third murder is pure chance.

73
00:04:56.041 --> 00:04:59.833
The ladies' toilet in an office building.

74
00:04:59.916 --> 00:05:03.333
You'd be very lucky
not to get caught or identified.

75
00:05:03.416 --> 00:05:05.333
So what is the conclusion?

76
00:05:05.416 --> 00:05:09.250
We think we're dealing
with a well-adjusted sociopath.

77
00:05:09.333 --> 00:05:12.125
but we have no idea
if he's about to go bananas

78
00:05:12.208 --> 00:05:14.583
or if he's still fully in control.

79
00:05:14.666 --> 00:05:16.041
What should we hope for?

80
00:05:16.125 --> 00:05:19.458
In the first case.
we're facing a massacre.

81
00:05:19.541 --> 00:05:21.500
but with a chance of catching him.

82
00:05:21.583 --> 00:05:24.208
In the second. there'll be
longer breaks between murders.

83
00:05:24.291 --> 00:05:26.625
but we probably
won't be able to catch him.

84
00:05:26.708 --> 00:05:30.250
It's the frying pan or the fire.
I don't know which you prefer?

85
00:05:31.333 --> 00:05:33.333
Okay. Thank you. Ståle.

86
00:05:34.041 --> 00:05:36.500
I would suggest that we start by

87
00:05:36.583 --> 00:05:40.916
bringing in everyone we've talked to
for a new round of interrogations.

88
00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:44.666
We'll have many eyes on us.
even from abroad.

89
00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:52.833
So you were at ABC Debt Collectors
to speak about hearing aids?

90
00:05:52.916 --> 00:05:55.583
My lawyer is getting old.
so I need new ones

91
00:05:55.666 --> 00:05:59.041
to make a legal assessment
of an agency agreement.

92
00:05:59.125 --> 00:06:03.583
Yeah. so you got in touch with lawyers
who specialize in debt collection?

93
00:06:03.666 --> 00:06:06.375
Yeah. but I didn't realize that
until during the meeting.

94
00:06:06.458 --> 00:06:10.750
I mean. the brief minute we got.
before all the commotion started.

95
00:06:10.833 --> 00:06:14.625
If you're getting a new lawyer. I assume
you've booked meetings with several.

96
00:06:14.708 --> 00:06:16.791
Can you tell me who?

97
00:06:16.875 --> 00:06:20.458
The law firms didn't want to meet me
until after the summer vacation.

98
00:06:20.541 --> 00:06:23.458
ABC Debt Collectors
were more accommodating.

99
00:06:23.541 --> 00:06:25.625
Am I a suspect of something?

100
00:06:26.208 --> 00:06:27.750
Yes. everyone's a suspect.

101
00:06:33.125 --> 00:06:35.166
Is that an accent I hear?

102
00:06:36.583 --> 00:06:40.500
Yeah. it's possible.
I... travel a lot abroad.

103
00:06:40.583 --> 00:06:43.458
- It might be something like that.
- Where do you travel to?

104
00:06:44.416 --> 00:06:46.625
Well. I have a small house in Thailand.

105
00:06:46.708 --> 00:06:50.166
I go to Switzerland
to visit the hearing aid manufacturer.

106
00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:54.416
But I travel mostly in Norway.
to hospitals and institutions and such.

107
00:06:54.500 --> 00:06:56.916
Are you married? Do you have a family?

108
00:06:57.500 --> 00:07:01.708
If thou wouldst behold that piece
of paper Skarre has been scribbling on.

109
00:07:01.791 --> 00:07:03.458
thou wouldst see that I do not.

110
00:07:03.541 --> 00:07:05.541
I live with Truls.

111
00:07:06.833 --> 00:07:09.041
Truls is a Shar Pei.

112
00:07:09.625 --> 00:07:10.708
A dog.

113
00:07:13.791 --> 00:07:17.166
Fine. Could you just tell me
what... happened?

114
00:07:17.250 --> 00:07:19.375
I think that your colleague Skarre--

115
00:07:19.458 --> 00:07:23.291
He's written it down. I get it.
but could you tell <i>me</i> what happened?

116
00:07:26.541 --> 00:07:28.583
- Hello.
- Yes. Can I help you?

117
00:07:28.666 --> 00:07:31.750
Yes. so. I have a meeting
with Halle in a few minutes.

118
00:07:31.833 --> 00:07:34.333
but five floors were a bit much for me.

119
00:07:34.416 --> 00:07:37.083
I asked the receptionist...

120
00:07:37.666 --> 00:07:39.000
Barbara Svendsen.

121
00:07:39.083 --> 00:07:41.166
I asked her for a glass of water.

122
00:07:41.250 --> 00:07:43.083
<i>and she went down the corridor.</i>

123
00:07:43.166 --> 00:07:44.166
<i>- Yeah.
- Yes.</i>

124
00:07:44.250 --> 00:07:47.791
But then she never returned.
so I went in to look for Halle.

125
00:07:47.875 --> 00:07:49.375
with whom I had an appointment.

126
00:07:50.958 --> 00:07:52.250
- Hi.
- Hi?

127
00:07:52.333 --> 00:07:54.541
- I'm Clausen.
- Clausen! Yes.

128
00:07:54.625 --> 00:07:57.250
Did you see anyone else
walk in or out of the ladies' room?

129
00:07:57.333 --> 00:08:00.250
No. I didn't see anyone else
apart from those who worked there.

130
00:08:00.333 --> 00:08:02.833
You know what.
I've said this many times already.

131
00:08:02.916 --> 00:08:06.916
I can see that. but there's nothing
about exactly which employee you saw.

132
00:08:08.458 --> 00:08:10.125
Everyone's a suspect. fine.

133
00:08:10.750 --> 00:08:12.625
Yeah. I need the room.

134
00:08:13.250 --> 00:08:14.125
You can leave.

135
00:08:14.875 --> 00:08:15.875
- Thanks.
- Not you.

136
00:08:16.625 --> 00:08:18.208
You can leave. you stay here.

137
00:08:19.833 --> 00:08:21.041
We're staying here.

138
00:08:25.916 --> 00:08:26.750
Continue.

139
00:08:27.250 --> 00:08:28.625
I saw the cleaner.

140
00:08:29.291 --> 00:08:31.958
But she disappeared
further down the corridor.

141
00:08:32.041 --> 00:08:33.166
We've talked to her.

142
00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:37.083
Yes. And then I saw...

143
00:08:37.166 --> 00:08:42.708
a guy in a suit...
who poured coffee by the coffee machine.

144
00:08:42.791 --> 00:08:47.416
and then he disappeared into
what I assume was his office.

145
00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:50.541
- There was the bike courier. of course.
- The bike courier?

146
00:08:50.625 --> 00:08:51.625
Yes.

147
00:08:51.708 --> 00:08:56.000
The bike courier walked out
right before I went to look for Halle.

148
00:08:56.083 --> 00:08:59.333
Technically. I guess he isn't
one of the employees.

149
00:08:59.416 --> 00:09:03.500
but he was there on business. so to speak.
Why are you looking at me like that?

150
00:09:03.583 --> 00:09:06.416
- What did he look like? Tall? Thin?
- Fuck if I know.

151
00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:09.375
How am I supposed to know that?
He was on his way out.

152
00:09:09.458 --> 00:09:12.041
- Like me. maybe. regular...
- Fat?

153
00:09:12.833 --> 00:09:14.708
Fat? You can't say...

154
00:09:14.791 --> 00:09:15.833
Just stay here.

155
00:09:22.958 --> 00:09:26.208
How quickly can you get me a list
of orders made to bike couriers

156
00:09:26.291 --> 00:09:27.375
on the murder day?

157
00:09:27.458 --> 00:09:30.291
- Pretty quickly. I think.
- But first. I need to...

158
00:09:30.375 --> 00:09:32.416
Call all bike courier companies
in the city.

159
00:09:32.500 --> 00:09:34.625
Look for a delivery or a pick-up at ABC.

160
00:09:34.708 --> 00:09:38.416
- You're not the one leading...
- Just do it.

161
00:09:40.666 --> 00:09:42.791
Did this Clausen give you a description?

162
00:09:42.875 --> 00:09:45.541
Yes. he had a black bike shirt. shorts.

163
00:09:45.625 --> 00:09:47.750
biking shoes that made a clicking noise.

164
00:09:47.833 --> 00:09:50.916
He was not sure of his height.
His face was hidden.

165
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:55.333
He had sunglasses and a bike helmet.
and interestingly. face mask.

166
00:09:55.416 --> 00:09:57.375
That is why Camilla Loen let him in.

167
00:09:58.166 --> 00:10:00.000
Of course. he just called the bell.

168
00:10:00.083 --> 00:10:02.625
Bike couriers are already masked
in front of the camera.

169
00:10:02.708 --> 00:10:05.791
<i>He came in with a bouquet of flowers
or an express package.</i>

170
00:10:06.291 --> 00:10:09.458
From the moment Clausen arrived
until he saw the bike courier leave.

171
00:10:09.541 --> 00:10:11.041
it had been over four minutes.

172
00:10:11.125 --> 00:10:13.000
A bike courier would run in.

173
00:10:13.083 --> 00:10:16.500
deliver and run out again.

174
00:10:16.583 --> 00:10:19.000
He wouldn't spend four minutes
dawdling around.

175
00:10:19.083 --> 00:10:23.458
I'll have people check for couriers
at the crime scenes.

176
00:10:23.541 --> 00:10:26.375
Yes. Hey. there's one more thing
we need to consider.

177
00:10:28.041 --> 00:10:30.708
If we should warn people
about unknown bike couriers.

178
00:10:30.791 --> 00:10:32.875
<i>- Okay. I'll talk to Møller.</i>
- Okay.

179
00:10:32.958 --> 00:10:33.875
<i>Hey. Harry.</i>

180
00:10:33.958 --> 00:10:36.333
Great fucking job.

181
00:10:51.166 --> 00:10:53.458
<i>One person has been confirmed deceased</i>

182
00:10:53.541 --> 00:10:56.833
<i>after the attack
on Korps motorcycle club yesterday.</i>

183
00:11:49.125 --> 00:11:50.083
<i>Hello?</i>

184
00:11:52.916 --> 00:11:53.833
Hello?

185
00:11:57.625 --> 00:11:58.791
Can I help you?

186
00:11:58.875 --> 00:12:01.541
Listen. I'm here on behalf of the police.

187
00:12:03.625 --> 00:12:07.583
Hey. those... star symbols
on your door here...

188
00:12:10.166 --> 00:12:11.541
The pentagram?

189
00:12:13.041 --> 00:12:13.916
It...

190
00:12:14.416 --> 00:12:16.083
Is there something wrong with it?

191
00:12:16.166 --> 00:12:18.625
No. I'm just wondering what they mean.

192
00:12:20.958 --> 00:12:26.000
The pentagram is an... old religious symbol.

193
00:12:26.583 --> 00:12:29.750
Found on gravestones
more than a thousand years old.

194
00:12:31.708 --> 00:12:34.750
Yeah. so it's a symbol for the good?

195
00:12:34.833 --> 00:12:36.750
Yes. ours is.

196
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:39.708
But...

197
00:12:40.833 --> 00:12:44.125
When the pentagram is
upside down. meaning...

198
00:12:44.833 --> 00:12:46.666
if there are two points pointing up...

199
00:12:48.250 --> 00:12:52.291
then you're entering
the field of demonology.

200
00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:54.166
Which is?

201
00:12:55.208 --> 00:12:57.166
The teachings of evil.

202
00:13:09.041 --> 00:13:11.625
So the bike courier lead gave us nothing?

203
00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:15.208
We have APBs on social media. radio. TV.

204
00:13:15.791 --> 00:13:17.666
Received 24 tips so far.

205
00:13:17.750 --> 00:13:20.583
They confirm what
we more or less already know.

206
00:13:21.708 --> 00:13:24.375
Contact the press
that had photographers at Carl Berner

207
00:13:24.458 --> 00:13:26.541
and see if they have
footage of the attendees.

208
00:13:26.625 --> 00:13:29.625
Honestly. that myth
about returning to the crime scene?

209
00:13:29.708 --> 00:13:32.041
If it is a sociopathic serial killer.

210
00:13:32.125 --> 00:13:35.541
he sees the investigation
as an exciting game

211
00:13:35.625 --> 00:13:37.791
he's playing with the police.

212
00:13:37.875 --> 00:13:38.708
Follow me.

213
00:13:40.291 --> 00:13:42.458
And what does Forensics say?

214
00:13:42.541 --> 00:13:44.750
That we are understaffed
and behind schedule.

215
00:13:44.833 --> 00:13:48.458
but also that we've put old corpses aside
to prioritize these ones.

216
00:13:48.541 --> 00:13:53.333
No semen. no skin. hair or blood.

217
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:56.416
And no signs of sexual assault.

218
00:13:56.500 --> 00:13:59.083
The only physical evidence
of a perpetrator

219
00:13:59.166 --> 00:14:01.208
is basically the bullet holes.

220
00:14:01.833 --> 00:14:04.333
- That is interesting.
- What is?

221
00:14:04.416 --> 00:14:07.000
That there are no signs of sexual assault.

222
00:14:07.500 --> 00:14:09.416
No. I guess it's not about sex. then.

223
00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:13.416
No. serial killings always have
a sexual motive. Always.

224
00:14:15.208 --> 00:14:17.833
Maybe we've got a Mr. Chance.

225
00:14:21.666 --> 00:14:26.750
He may not need to touch her
to be sexually satisfied.

226
00:14:26.833 --> 00:14:31.250
Maybe the murder itself
or the sight of the corpse is enough.

227
00:14:32.708 --> 00:14:34.166
What about Lisbeth Barli?

228
00:14:34.666 --> 00:14:38.166
We've examined her finger.
and what we can tell you.

229
00:14:38.250 --> 00:14:42.166
is that the surface of the cuts
suggest that the same knife or tool

230
00:14:42.250 --> 00:14:45.500
has been used in all three cases.

231
00:14:45.583 --> 00:14:47.791
What about the weapons
at the crime scenes?

232
00:14:48.291 --> 00:14:51.375
The tests confirm
that they were used in the murders.

233
00:14:51.458 --> 00:14:53.791
but the serial numbers
have been filed down.

234
00:14:53.875 --> 00:14:56.458
The same file marks
as on most of the confiscated weapons.

235
00:14:56.541 --> 00:15:00.958
The city's overflowing with guns.
It's turning into Montana fast.

236
00:15:05.916 --> 00:15:07.833
Maya. the Barli case?

237
00:15:07.916 --> 00:15:11.250
We're writing that Toya Harang takes over
after her sister in <i>Pygmalion.</i>

238
00:15:11.333 --> 00:15:14.666
- The copy should be ready before lunch.
- Okay. Any quotes?

239
00:15:14.750 --> 00:15:18.416
Willy Barli: "'The show must go on'
is more than a simple cliché."

240
00:15:18.500 --> 00:15:23.500
"Our business is serious. and I know
Lisbeth is with us no matter what."

241
00:15:23.583 --> 00:15:25.375
"The situation has deeply affected us."

242
00:15:25.458 --> 00:15:27.958
"Still. we try to use that energy
in a positive manner."

243
00:15:28.041 --> 00:15:30.041
"The play will be a homage to Lisbeth."

244
00:15:30.125 --> 00:15:33.875
I like the feelgood angle on that.
we need some of that too.

245
00:15:33.958 --> 00:15:36.500
Everything is now
about the Bike Courier Killer.

246
00:15:36.583 --> 00:15:38.416
Put any other work you have aside.

247
